{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: provider-as-requester-eu-lab_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates TWO active FSH instances that model the requesting provider for
    a EU laboratory order:

      1. PractitionerRole  — the requester's role, linked to their organisation.
      2. Organization      — the organisation on behalf of which the request
                             is made.

    A third instance (Practitioner) is defined in the template source but is
    **commented out** and produces no output. See "Commented-out Practitioner"
    section below.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    PractitionerRole : PractitionerRoleEu   (EU lab profile variant; not EuCore)
    Organization     : OrganizationEu       (EU lab profile variant; not EuCore)

  CONTEXT — EU Lab vs EPS
    This template targets the EU Laboratory Report context and therefore uses
    the `PractitionerRoleEu` / `OrganizationEu` profiles rather than the
    `*EuCore` profiles used by provider-as-primarycarephysician-eps_fsh.twig.
    The requester is the clinician who ordered the lab tests, not the physician
    responsible for the patient's overall care.

  setInstance() USE
    Only the PractitionerRole instance is registered via `setInstance()`:
      → "Instance-PractitionerRole-<requester.instancerole>"
    The Organization instance uses direct `{{ }}` interpolation and is NOT
    registered in the `twigit()` return array.

  ⚠  ADDRESS VARIABLE MISMATCH
    The Organisation's address sub-elements are gated on `provider.*` variables
    rather than `requester.*` variables:
      {% if provider.address is not empty %}  ← uses `provider`, not `requester`
      {% if provider.city    is not empty %}
      …
    This appears to be a copy-paste carry-over from
    provider-as-primarycarephysician-eps_fsh.twig. If the `provider` context
    object is populated alongside `requester` in the calling PHP code this will
    work, but may produce unexpected results or empty address blocks if only
    `requester.*` is supplied. This should be reviewed and potentially changed
    to `requester.address`, `requester.city`, etc. if a separate address is
    needed for the requesting organisation.

  COMMENTED-OUT PRACTITIONER BLOCK
    A Practitioner instance block is present in the source but fully suppressed
    by wrapping it in Twig block comments (`{ # … # }`). The block is split across
    two separate comment segments due to the presence of an inner `{ # … # }` tag
    (Twig comments cannot be nested — the inner tag terminates the first outer
    comment, so a second outer comment is opened immediately to continue the
    suppression through to the closing `# }`):

      Segment 1: {# } … { # populate .text # }   ← closed by inner tag's # }
      Segment 2: {# } … # }                      ← closes remainder of block

    The net effect is that the entire Practitioner block produces no output.
    The commented-out block references `provider.*` variables (not `requester.*`)
    and would need variable-name alignment before activation.
    To reinstate the Practitioner instance, remove the outer comment delimiters
    and verify all variable references.

  NO HTML OUTPUT
    Both %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% sections are intentionally left empty.
    Each active FSH instance carries only a minimal plain-text `text.div`.

  ORGANISATION IDENTIFIER
    The Organisation identifier is caller-supplied (`requester.orgidentifier`)
    under the HL7 Europe OID namespace (`HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID`). No UUID is
    generated for this identifier — it is a stable business id.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                         │ Type     │ Description                              │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ requester.instancerole           │ string   │ UUID / id for the PractitionerRole.      │
  │                                  │          │ Registered via setInstance().            │
  │ requester.instanceorg            │ string   │ UUID / id for the Organization.          │
  │ requester.orgidentifier          │ string   │ Business identifier value for the        │
  │                                  │          │ requesting Organisation (under            │
  │                                  │          │ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID).                   │
  │ requester.orgname                │ string   │ Display name of the requesting           │
  │                                  │          │ organisation.                            │
  │ provider.address                 │ string?  │ Optional address line — note: address    │
  │                                  │          │ fields use `provider.*` not `requester.*`│
  │                                  │          │ (see Address Variable Mismatch above).   │
  │ provider.city                    │ string?  │ Optional city name (same note).          │
  │ provider.postcode                │ string?  │ Optional postal code (same note).        │
  │ provider.country                 │ string?  │ Optional country (same note).            │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the Organisation identifier system URI.

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-07
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

{#
  ── Instance 1: PractitionerRole ────────────────────────────────────────────
  The requester's role, linked to their organisation. No Practitioner reference
  is included (the Practitioner instance is commented out; see file header).
  Registered via setInstance() — the only tracked instance in this template.
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-PractitionerRole-" ~ requester.instancerole) }}
InstanceOf: PractitionerRoleEu
Title: "Practitioner Role (EPS) Requester"
Description: "Practitioner Role Requester"
Usage: #inline
* id           = "{{ requester.instancerole }}"
* organization = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ requester.instanceorg }})
{# Minimal narrative — identifies the role by its id #}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
Provider Role Id: {{ requester.instancerole }}
</div>
"""

{#
  ── Instance 2: Organization ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The requesting organisation — the practice or department that placed the lab
  order. Identified by a caller-supplied business identifier (not a generated
  UUID) under the HL7 Europe OID namespace.
  Note: Instance id interpolated directly — NOT registered via setInstance().

  ⚠ Address fields use `provider.*` variables — see "Address Variable Mismatch"
    in the file header. Verify the calling context populates `provider.*` as
    expected, or update to `requester.*` if separate address data is required.
#}
Instance: Instance-Organization-{{ requester.instanceorg }}
InstanceOf: OrganizationEu
Title: "Organization Requester"
Description: "Organization Requester"
Usage: #inline
* id = "{{ requester.instanceorg }}"

{# Business identifier under the HL7 Europe OID namespace #}
* identifier.system           = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier.value            = "{{ requester.orgidentifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

* name = "{{ requester.orgname }}"

{# ⚠ Address gated on provider.* — see Address Variable Mismatch note #}
{% if provider.address is not empty %}
* address.line = "{{ provider.address }}"
{% endif %}
{% if provider.city is not empty %}
* address.city = "{{ provider.city }}"
{% endif %}
{% if provider.postcode is not empty %}
* address.postalCode = "{{ provider.postcode }}"
{% endif %}
{% if provider.country is not empty %}
* address.country = "{{ provider.country }}"
{% endif %}

{# Minimal narrative — shows the requesting organisation name #}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
Provider Organization: {{ requester.orgname }}
</div>
"""

{#
  ── Instance 3: Practitioner (COMMENTED OUT) ────────────────────────────────
  The block generates a PractitionerEu instance for the requesting physician.
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Practitioner-" ~ provider.instanceprovider) }}
InstanceOf: PractitionerEu
Title: "Practitioner Requester"
Description: "Practitioner Requester"
Usage: #inline
* id = "{{ provider.instanceprovider }}"
* name.prefix = "{{ provider.providernameprefix }}"
* name.given[+] ="{{ provider.providernamegiven }}"
* name.family = "{{ provider.providernamefamily }}"
{# populate .text #}

* text.status = #generated
* text.div =""""
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ provider.providernameprefix ~ " " ~ provider.providernamegiven ~ " " ~ provider.providernamefamily }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# No HEAD output — this template produces no HTML table. #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# No HTML output — this template produces no HTML table. #}
